STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
David B. PORTER, Appellant. WD 79768 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: October 31, 2017
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied December 14, 2017 Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, and Christine Lesicko, Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Damien de Loyola, District Defender, Kansas City, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Before Division IV: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Chief Judge, and Gary D. Witt and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Mr. David B. Porter appeals from the judgment entered by the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, following a jury trial in which he was found guilty of two counts of first-degree child molestation. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 30.25(b).
